    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-31T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="587"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/25881: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-31T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Embassy’s number 63, August 29. Reassure Minister of Foreign Relations that
                    there is no immediate prospect of recognition of Mexican Government and that
                    when recognition is contemplated Belgian Government will be notified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
